name: Lady of the Boughs
description: Inspired by the German expressionist movement. The first in a series of a personal mythology that I'm developing. The Lady of the Boughs is born of the discarded multitude of human garments. They shroud her beauty as nature is shrouded by the waste of mankind. Woe to those whom her gaze falls upon, for they shall be drawn into the depths of the woods, never to return. ~9x12 on heavy stock white paper

name: The Hand of God (lightning)
description: Three-color screen print inspired by Norse mythology. A modern interpretation of Thor, the god of thunder. 11x8.5 On light blue cardstock.
